[SN]TITLE[SN]
Andrew Fox: Stevenage sign Peterborough United left-back

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
League Two side Stevenage have signed left-back Andrew Fox on a deal which starts on 1 July, when his Peterborough United contract ends.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The 23-year-old made 22 appearances for Posh after joining last summer and also had a brief spell in the National League at Kidderminster Harriers.
Fox moved to the ABAX Stadium after spending four years studying at university in Texas.
He follows the Boro signings of keeper Jamie Jones and striker Matt Godden.
